This product includes third-party components.

Every external component is selected as a latest stable release, pinned by
exact version and verified digest, and recorded with an SPDX license
identifier in `toolchain.lock.json`. That manifest is the authoritative
record; this file is a human-readable summary of it.

Components currently pinned:

- Zig compiler — MIT — https://ziglang.org/

Component classes permitted by the architecture but not yet adopted, each
requiring an architecture decision record before it is pinned:

- AOSP platform and its supported Linux kernel line
- Cuttlefish reference-device tooling
- QEMU
- Wasmtime and the WebAssembly Component Model tooling
- SQLite
- cryptographic libraries selected after security review
- UI, graphics, text, and media libraries selected after the shell spike

No component is adopted because it is popular. Regenerate the summary above
from the manifest rather than editing it by hand.
